canonical:
  title: 春日
  author: 徐居正
  language: lzh
  text: 金入垂楊玉謝梅小池新水碧於苔春愁春興誰深淺燕子不來花未開
  rtl: true
  vertical: true
lzh_formatted:
  title: 春日
  author: 徐居正
  language: lzh
  text: 金入垂楊玉謝梅。小池新水碧於苔。春愁春興誰深淺。燕子不來花未開。
korean:
  title: 춘일
  author: 서거정
  language: kor
  text: |-
    금빛은 실버들에 들어가고 옥은 매화를 이별하는데
    작은 못의 새로운 물은 이끼보다 푸르다
    봄 시름과 봄 흥의 어느 것이 깊고 옅은가
    제비도 오지 않고 꽃도 피지 않았네
  url: https://db.itkc.or.kr/dir/item?itemId=BT#dir/node?dataId=ITKC_BT_1365A_1450_020_0100&viewSync=OT
  footnotes: []
english:
  title: Spring Day
  author: Seo Geo-jeong
  language: eng
  text: |-
    Gold gleams through trailing willows, jade parts from the plum blossom.
    The small pond's fresh water grows greener than moss.
    Which cuts deeper—spring's sorrow or spring's delight?
    The swallows have not yet come, and flowers remain unborn.
  footnotes:
  - key: ''
    value: The contrasting images of gold (willows) and jade (plums) represent the passing of early spring, while the vivid green of the pond suggests renewal and life stirring beneath the surface.
  - key: ''
    value: The poet questions whether melancholy or joy dominates this transitional moment of spring—a common meditation in East Asian poetry on the ambivalent nature of seasonal change.
